  "script": "There's an animal that hits speeds a race car can't match, and it does it falling out of the sky. It's the peregrine falcon. When it spots a target, it folds its wings and dives in what's called a stoop, reaching over two hundred miles an hour. At that speed, special baffles in its nose let it keep breathing, and a third eyelid wipes its eyes clear. It hits its prey mid-air with a closed foot, a strike so hard the impact alone kills. The fastest animal alive isn't the cheetah. So what happens to a pigeon that never sees it coming?",
